#	Requirement Name	User Stories Needed (IDs/titles)	Inputs Needed from Other Sub‑Systems	Downstream Sub‑Systems Depending on This Output	Key BRs (IDs)		BR ID	BR


1	Shift Assignment Management	As a System Admin/HR Admin, I want to assign shifts to employees (individually, by department, or by position) and manage their statuses (Approved, Cancelled, Expired, etc.) so that work schedules are properly maintained and updated.	Employee Profile, Organizational Structure	Time Management	BR-TM-02, BR-TM-05, BR-TM-03, BR-TM-04		BR-TM-01	Roles for time management must be defined by the System Admin. Line Managers and HR approve or reject time management permissions.


2	Shift Configuration & Types	As an HR Manager/System Admin, I want to define and configure shift types (Normal, Split, Overnight, Rotational, etc.) and their corresponding names so that different work arrangements are supported consistently.	None	Time Management	BR-TM-03, BR-TM-04		BR-TM-02	Shifts must be assigned per employee for a defined term and hold statuses (Approved, Cancelled, Entered, Expired, Postponed, Rejected, Submitted).


3	Custom Scheduling Rules	As an HR Manager, I want to define flexible and custom scheduling rules (e.g., flex-in/flex-out hours, custom weekly patterns like 4 days on/3 off) so that the organization can accommodate diverse work styles.	None	Time Management	BR-TM-04, BR-TM-10		BR-TM-03	The system must support multiple shift types (Normal, Split, Overnight, Mission, Rotational) with start and end dates.


4	Shift Expiry Notifications	As an HR Admin, I want to be notified when a shift assignment is nearing expiry so that schedules can be renewed or reassigned.	Time Management	Notifications	BR-TM-05		BR-TM-04	The system must support multiple shift names (Fixed Core Hours, Flex-Time, Rotational, Split, Custom Weekly Patterns, Overtime).


5	Clock-In/Out	As an Employee, I want to clock in/out using ID	External Excel Sheet	Time Management	BR-TM-06		BR-TM-05	Shift schedules must be assignable by Department, Position, or Individual.


6	Manual Attendance Correction	As a Line Manager, I want to record or correct attendance manually so that missing punches can be updated accurately.	Organizational Structure	Time Management	BR-TM-06, BR-TM-24		BR-TM-06	Time-in/out must be captured via Biometric, Web Login, Mobile App (GPS optional), or Manual Input (with audit trail).

7	Flexible Punch Handling	As an Employee/System Admin, I want to support multiple clock-ins/outs per day or restrict to first-in/last-out, so that the system adapts to different work styles.	Time Management	Time Management	BR-TM-11		BR-TM-07	Attendance data must follow HR rounding rules (nearest interval, ceiling/floor, alignment, first in/last out).

8	Missed Punch Management	As an Employee/Line Manager/Payroll Officer, I want the system to flag missed punches and send alerts	Time Management	Notifications, Payroll	BR-TM-14		BR-TM-08	Overtime/Short Time must be calculated according to organizational policies (types, categories, implementation rules, calculation methods).

9	Attendance-to-Payroll Sync	As an HR Admin, I want attendance records to sync daily with payroll and leave systems so that data remains consistent.	Time Management	Payroll, Leaves	BR-TM-22		BR-TM-09	Early/Lateness per shift must follow HR rules (grace period, penalty thresholds, escalation).

10	Overtime & Short Time Configuration	As an HR Manager, I want to configure overtime and short-time rules (including weekend, holiday, and pre-approval types) so that attendance and payroll comply with policies.	None	Time Management	BR-TM-08		BR-TM-10	The system must restrict early/late clock-ins based on configured shifts and rules.


11	Lateness & Penalty Rules	As an HR Manager, I want to set grace periods, lateness thresholds, and automatic deductions so that penalties are applied fairly and consistently.	None	Time Management	BR-TM-09		BR-TM-11	The system must allow multiple punches per day, or alternatively use first in/last out.


12	Repeated Lateness Handling	As an HR Admin/Manager, I want the system to flag repeated lateness for disciplinary tracking so that repeated offenders can be identified.	Time Management	Performance Management	BR-TM-09, BR-TM-16		BR-TM-12	Clock-ins must be tagged with location, terminal ID, or device.


13	Attendance Correction Requests	As an Employee, I want to submit correction requests for missing or incorrect punches and track their approval status.	Time Management	Time Management	BR-TM-15		BR-TM-13	Attendance devices must sync automatically once reconnected online.


14	Time Exception Approval Workflow	As a Line Manager/HR Admin, I want to review, approve, or reject attendance-related requests (corrections, overtime, permissions) and escalate unresolved ones automatically after deadlines.	Time Management	Time Management / Notifications 	BR-TM-01, BR-TM-15, BR-TM-20		BR-TM-14	Missed punches/late sign-ins must be handled via auto-flagging, notifications, or payroll blocking.


15	Permission Validation Rules	As an HR Admin, I want to define limits for permission durations and ensure only approved permissions affect payroll.	Time Management	Time Management / Payroll	BR-TM-18, BR-TM-16		BR-TM-15	Employees must be able to submit correction requests (reason + time) via ESS, routed to Line Manager for approval.


16	Vacation Package Integration	As an HR Manager, I want employee vacation packages linked to their schedules so that time off is automatically reflected in attendance and planning.	Leaves Module	Time Management	BR-TM-19		BR-TM-16	Permission policies must define types of Over/Short time (Early In, Late Out, Out of Hours, Total).


17	Holiday & Rest Day Configuration	As a System Admin/HR Admin, I want to define national holidays, organizational holidays, and weekly rest days so that no shifts or attendance penalties are applied during those times.	Leaves Module	Time Management (Penalty suppression)	BR-TM-19		BR-TM-17	Permissions must be tied to valid dates (contract start, financial calendar, probation date).


18	Escalation for Pending Requests Before Payroll Cut-Off	As a System Admin/HR Admin, I want leave or time requests to escalate automatically if not reviewed before the monthly payroll cut-off date so that payroll processing is not delayed.	Payroll, Time Management	Notifications	BR-TM-20		BR-TM-18	Over/Short time permissions can be Accepted or Rejected, impacting payroll and benefits.


19	Overtime & Exception Reports	As an HR or Payroll Officer, I want to view and export overtime and exception attendance reports so that payroll and compliance checks are accurate.	Time Management	Analytics / Payroll	BR-TM-21		BR-TM-19	Vacation packages, national holidays, organizational holidays, and weekly rest days must be linked to shift schedules.


20	Cross-Module Data Synchronization	As an HR Manager, I want attendance and time management data synchronized with payroll and leave modules to maintain consistent records.	Time Management	Payroll, Leaves	BR-TM-22		BR-TM-20	Unreviewed employee requests must auto-escalate after a defined time or before payroll cutoff.
							BR-TM-21	HR and Line Managers must have access to attendance summaries, lateness logs, and overtime reports.											BR-TM-22	All time management data must sync daily with payroll, benefits, and leave modules.




Step	Actor	Action / Process	Supporting User Stories (US) and Rules (BR)	output and data flow			BR-TM-23	Reports must be exportable in multiple formats (Excel, Access, Text).

1: Shift Configuration & Types	HR Manager / System Admin	Defines and configures standard shift types (Normal, Split, Overnight, Rotational) and naming templates that will be used across the organization.	US 2	Shift templates are created and stored for use in scheduling; foundational data for later attendance tracking.			BR-TM-24	All edits/changes/cancellations must be timestamped and audit-tracked.

2: Shift Assignment Management	HR Admin / System Admin	Assigns configured shifts to employees (individually, by department, or position). Updates shift statuses (Approved, Cancelled, Expired).	US 1	Employee schedules generated; valid shift assignments created for attendance validation.			BR-TM-25	The system must maintain continuous data backup with a retention policy.

3: Define Custom Scheduling Rules	HR Manager	Sets custom scheduling logic such as flexible hours, rotational work weeks, or compressed patterns (4-on/3-off).	US 3	Scheduling flexibility applied; outputs feed into attendance validation logic.

4: Shift Expiry Notification & Renewal	System / HR Admin	Sends notifications when a shift assignment nears expiry, prompting renewal or reassignment.	US 4	Alerts generated for HR; expiring shifts either renewed or archived.

5: Employee Clock-In / Clock-Out	Employee	Clocks in/out using ID validating against assigned shifts and rest days.	US 5	Attendance records created and timestamped; data logged for validation.

6: Manual Attendance Correction	Line Manager	Reviews and corrects attendance in case of missing or invalid punches.	US 6	Corrected attendance record stored; audit log updated.
7: Flexible Punch Handling	System Admin / Employee	Enables or restricts multiple punches per day (e.g., first-in/last-out vs. multiple).	US 7	Punch validation logic applied; affects attendance data calculations.


8: Missed Punch Management & Alerts	Employee / Line Manager	Flags missed punches and sends automated alerts to employees and managers for correction.	US 8	Notification records sent; pending corrections logged in system.

9: Overtime & Short Time Configuration	HR Manager	Configures overtime, short-time, and weekend work rules, including approval requirements.	US 10	Overtime policies defined; stored for payroll and approval workflow.


10: Lateness & Penalty Rules Setup	HR Manager	Sets lateness thresholds, grace periods, and automatic penalty triggers.	US 11	Lateness configurations active; real-time penalty calculations enabled.


11: Repeated Lateness Handling	HR Admin / Manager System	flags repeated lateness for disciplinary tracking and escalation.	US 12	Escalate after threshold reached. Disciplinary flags; performance reports updated.

12: Attendance Correction Requests	Employee	Submits correction requests for missing or incorrect punches and tracks their approval status.	US 13	Correction request generated; pending approval workflow initiated.

13: Time Exception Approval Workflow	Line Manager / HR Admin	Reviews, approves, or rejects time-related requests (corrections, overtime, permissions). Escalates unreviewed ones automatically.	US 14	Approved or rejected requests finalized; audit trail maintained.
14: Holiday & Rest Day Configuration	System Admin / HR Admin	Defines national holidays, organizational holidays, and weekly rest days to suppress penalties.	US 17	Holiday master list created; integrated into shift and attendance checks.

15: Vacation Package Integration	HR Manager	Links employee vacation entitlements to attendance schedules for automatic reflection of time off.	US 16	Attendance and leave data unified; leave deductions auto-calculated.


16: Payroll Synchronization	System / HR Admin	Syncs attendance, overtime, and penalty data with payroll and leave systems daily.	US 20, 9	Payroll system updated with validated time data.


17: Reporting & Analytics Generation	HR Officer / Payroll Officer	Generates overtime, exception, and penalty reports for review and auditing.	US 19	Exportable reports and analytics dashboards generated.


18: Escalation Before Payroll Cut-Off	System / HR Admin	Automatically escalates any pending requests (corrections, permissions, approvals) before payroll finalization.	US 18	Escalation alerts sent; ensures clean payroll closure.